HEADWORD: Alosa
<hw>Alosa</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>the genus comprising the most common
varieties of shad. It replaces the older term
<altname><gen>Clupea</gen></altname>. See also <er>shad</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Alosa</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
